OL,3,CFour-nation summit needed now to
OL,4,Ctackle child poverty, says Flynn
OL,6,FHe confirmed the SNP will press ahead
OL,7,Fwith its amendment calling for the two-
OL,8,Fchild benefit cap to be scrapped
OL,9,Fimmediately, with a vote on it
OL,10,Fexpected to take place next week.
OL,12,FIn his letter, Mr Flynn said
OL,13,FWestminster cuts and Brexit had seen
OL,14,Fthe UK become "one of the poorest and
OL,15,Fmost unequal countries among our
OL,16,FEuropean neighbours".
OL,18,FHe added: "That will only change with
OL,19,Fconcerted action and substantial
OL,20,Finvestment from the UK Government,
OL,21,Fwhich has been severely lacking.
